{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyAt.html#Mathlib.Tactic.tacticApply_At_\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticApply_At_</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`apply t at i` uses forward reasoning with `t` at the hypothesis `i`.\nExplicitly, if `t : α₁ → ⋯ → αᵢ → ⋯ → αₙ` and `i` has type `αᵢ`, then this tactic adds\nmetavariables/goals for any terms of `αⱼ` for `j = 1, …, i-1`,\nthen replaces the type of `i` with `αᵢ₊₁ → ⋯ → αₙ` by applying those metavariables and the\noriginal `i`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyAt.html#Mathlib.Tactic.tacticApply_At_","kind":"def","line":24,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.tacticApply_At_","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyAt.lean#L24-L43"}}],"imports":["Init","Lean.Elab.Tactic.ElabTerm","Mathlib.Lean.Meta.Basic","Mathlib.Init"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.ApplyAt"}